(598, 120, 'tl_article', 512, 1506081948, 'text', 'a:2:{s:4:\"unit\";s:2:\"h1\";s:5:\"value\";s:24:\"But what was Building 7?\";}', '<p>Officially called WTC-7, it was a 47-story building standing at 190 meters tall. The building was owned by a wealthy real estate developer, Larry Silverstein. A man who made an enormous profit from 9/11, insurance companies paid him around $4.5 billion dollars after the attack. The building was rentend out by many tennants including the Soloman Brothers who owned 64% of the building and many US government offices such as the Department of Defence (DOD), the Central Intelligence Agency (CIA), the Secret Service and the New York Emergency Management, a top floor command center managed by the former mayor of Now York, Rudy Guliani .[nbsp]<br><br>Next to the twin towers, Tower 7 looked tiny, but if this building were in any other city, say Berlin or Paris it would have looked much bigger. The tallest building in Berlin is only 125 meters tall, much smaller than WTC-7. Imagine if the tallest building in Berlin fell down on it\'s own and hardly anybody even knew about it? If you ask people, almost nobody has ever heard of Building 7 but everybody knows about the Twin Towers. Officially, Tower 7 was the third worst building collapse in human history, next to the Twin Towers. The Twin Towers and Tower 7 were also the only buildings in history ever known to have been destroyed by burning fires[nbsp]</p>', '', NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'above', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', 0, 'ascending', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 4, 0, 0, '', '', '', '', NULL, 'bwa-GtWp4h4', NULL, 'a:2:{i:0;s:0:\"\";i:1;s:0:\"\";}', '', 0, 300, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', NULL, '', 'a:2:{i:0;s:0:\"\";i:1;s:0:\"\";}', 'a:2:{i:0;s:0:\"\";i:1;s:0:\"\";}', '', '', '', 'ascending', 0, '', '', '', '', 'com_default', 0, '', 10, '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 0, 0, '', NULL, '', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 0, '