(718, 145, 'tl_article', 384, 1506083853, 'text', 'a:2:{s:4:\"unit\";s:2:\"h1\";s:5:\"value\";s:19:\"The art of the coin\";}', '<p>So how does Bitcoin really work and who controls it? The answer is that nobody controls Bitcoin. Bitcoin uses Blockchain and Hashing technology to keep a record of Bitcoin all over the world</p>\n<p>When Bitcoin is spent or sold, there must be a record of this[nbsp]<u>transaction</u>. With real money, this transaction record is kept on the computers and servers of the big banks, which are all connected to central banks like the Bank of England or the European Central Bank for example</p>', '', NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'above', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', 0, 'ascending', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 4, 0, 0, '', '', '', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', '', 0, 300, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', NULL, '', 'a:2:{i:0;s:0:\"\";i:1;s:0:\"\";}', 'a:2:{i:0;s:0:\"\";i:1;s:0:\"\";}', '', '', '', 'ascending', 0, '', '', '', '', 'com_default', 0, '', 10, '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 0, 0, '', NULL, '', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', ''),
