INSERT INTO `tl_search` (`id`, `pid`, `tstamp`, `title`, `url`, `text`, `filesize`, `checksum`, `protected`, `groups`, `language`) VALUES
(1, 54, 1506361411, 'Welcome', 'http://localhost/ContaoMeta.0.1/index.php/welcome.html', 'Welcome Welcome to Sam Systems English with Sam Face to face English classes online with a British native speaker travelling the world. Come and explore it with me in English Who we are? Hi, I\'m Sam, the creator of SamLernen. Here I offer everyone an exciting new way of learning English online, for work, for school or for your own personal development. I am a TEFL certified digital nomad who travels Europe and teaches online. I created SamLernen to provide our own exciting platform to teach and organise our courses and communication with our language learners. We believe that the best way to teach English is to offer interesting and exiting content where we learn English through discussion and analysis of world events, philosophy, history. We also work on creative web projects together, using internet technologies to make it even more interactive. The future of learning is here. Skype Lessons I give face-to-face Skype lessons for individuals and groups. The lessons are 45-minutes long and cost 20 Euros per lessons. For native speaks of Spanish, German or Dutch I teach all levels, and at intermediate level for native speakers of all other languages. Together we focus on speaking, as it is most important, and through homework and working projects, we perfect grammar and written skills. You only need a camera, a microphone and the internet. Skype is free! Learning by doing You learn more when you have fun. Simple as that..and I like to create stuff. Learning by doing provides a strong visual connection to the vocabulary learned in the lesson. We share all the cool stuff we make with others so they can enjoy and learn from it. Mind mapping We use interactive mindmapping to write down and save our ideas about a lesson. For example, we read a chapter of a book together and put in the words we learned together, we then connect those words to ideas and related words and topics Creative projects We use free real time collaborative software to create awesome posters, websites and designs. To make our topics more interesting, we create our own realistic newspaper article or infographic for it. We can edit and look at it again later. Homework has never been so fun. Coding Coding is a fantastic way to learn English for the technical minded. After designing our websites, it\'s fun to make them into a reality. Learning the basics of HTML and CSS teaches us a lot of useful web skills and because it\'s all in English using English command statements, we learn double! Learning Style I think differently and I am definitely not not politically correct. I say what I want and you should too! Our lessons are a place for free discussion and debate. We like to teach English by discovering what the language really has to offer us. We learn by taking a closer look at world events, music, crime, drugs, history, new technologies and travel. We encourage co-operation and the involvement of friends. Anything that makes learning more fun, makes it easier. You can do a course online with your friends/colleagues in the same room or using different computers. The more people, the more fun. Login in and Learn With SamLernen, you have the option to make an account and login. I only activate sign-up requests from clients. When you are signed up, you can organise all of your course work and your lesson times. This is very helpful, as it makes it more easier to access your course information when you are using a work computer or a mobile.When you are logged in, you also have other options like managing your payments, tracking your progress and accessing premium content Lessons We\'ve written a wide range of articles and lessons all about the most interesting topics from places and events all over the world. We read these articles together during our Skype lessons and use them to practise on reading, listening and speaking skills. We also pick apart the words and paragraphs to understand the grammar und writing techniques. The Expansion of Amazon Amazon is a HUGE company and it\'s growing like a cancer! Its customer base grows everyday. Thousands of Amazon deliveries are on their way to their destination as you read this. Will they all soon be delivered by drones? What plans does Amazon have for taking over the world? Read more to find out! How will China affect our future? The last 30 years has seen the nation of China grow to epic proportions and at a breakneck speed. China is on a path to become the worlds greatest economic power. How will this affect the future of Westerners who have grown up BEING in the group of the most powerful and successful countries in the world. Investing in Thailand Thailand is a beautiful and busy country. Its economy has grown significantly in the last few decades. We take a look at some example Thai proprerty for sale and role play how to wisely invest our money, which properties to chose and which ones are the best investments for the future Contao Demo,', 22.21, '7459d69c96b83b74a86a3ea9e54fd391', '', 0x30, 'en'),
(2, 51, 1506266602, 'Stories', 'http://localhost/ContaoMeta.0.1/index.php/stories.html', 'Stories Articles that I have written Stories for learning Many Skype lessons involve reading an article together, analysing it and talking about it. In your lesson calendar you can see which topics and stories we will be reading for each lesson. It may help to read the article before the lesson if you are unsure of the vocabulary. Articles Here are many articles for English learners. Leave a comment Top 3 Stories Is Macron the next Trump Who is Frances new president and where did he come from? Why did the French people decide on such a person and what will he bring to France? In this article we compare him to President Donald Trump of the USA. Although the two make not look like it, they are very similar as head of states. The Expansion of Amazon Amazon is a HUGE company and it\'s growing like a cancer! Its customer base grows everyday. Thousands of Amazon deliveries are on their way to their destination as you read this. Will they all soon be delivered by drones? What plans does Amazon have for taking over the world? Read more to find out! I am my Facebook and it is me Facebook is used on a massive scale everyday. Creating terrabytes of internet traffic and filling enormous databases with all your personal details. What are the effects of this massive social experiment and what is Facebook really doing with our data? Contao Demo,', 18.67, '4788c5d25fa329fe9e35f55442c127ec', '', 0x30, 'en'),
(3, 105, 1506266603, 'What the f*&^%$£ is Bitcoin', 'http://localhost/ContaoMeta.0.1/index.php/what-the-f-is-bitcoin.html', 'What the f*&^%$£ is Bitcoin English lesson about BitCoin What is f^%$%£ is BitCoin and should I start using it? The rise of digital currencies Bitcoin is a digital currency which uses a new form of technology. It is not like British Pounds or Euros because Bitcoins do not exist as notes or as coins. They exists only as digital money and is stored on servers over the internet. Many people are suspicious of Bitcoin because they cannot see or touch it and need the internet to use it, whereas other people claim that Bitcoin is the currency of the future and is a good investment because it will become more valuable in the future. An interesting fact is that 95% of all the money in the world is digital or some kind of promissory note, this means that only 5% of all money can be held in your hands. The art of the coin So how does Bitcoin really work and who controls it? The answer is that nobody controls Bitcoin. Bitcoin uses Blockchain and Hashing technology to keep a record of Bitcoin all over the world When Bitcoin is spent or sold, there must be a record of this transaction. With real money, this transaction record is kept on the computers and servers of the big banks, which are all connected to central banks like the Bank of England or the European Central Bank for example Questions - Do you think all currencies will be digital in the future? - If money only exists as digital money, does it exist at all? - What is the advantage/disadvantage of having millions of records on the internet instead of having records controlled by the banks? Which banks keep BitCoin records? No banks do. The records are kept on millions of private computers and servers. People who keep Bitcoin records are called Bitcoin Miners and the records are called \"blocks\". Anyone and everyone can be a Bitcoin Miner and miners can slowly earn Bitcoins by doing keeping these records. What about inflation? All currencies today fall under the category of Fiat Currencies. That means that these currencies are not backed by gold or silver or anything valuable (a.k.a commodities). What does this mean? It means that governments can print as much money as they like and cause inflation! There is only a limited number of Bitcoins in existance, and most of them have not yet been mined (like Gold). So although the value of Bitcoin goes up and down, this value cannot be directly controlled by the government by printing more or less mon Some market data Have a look at the Bitcoin price graph. Is the price going up or down at the moment? Over the last 2 years, the price of BitCoin has fluctuated enormously. When bringing up the topic of BitCoin with many people, they often remark about how somebody offered them to buy 1 Bitcoin at 300 dollars and how they could have been rich if they would have taken it. Roll play Imagine you are a Bitcoin advisor. Your partner wants to invest in Bitcoin. Should they? Here are some questions you might get - Is Bitcoin a stable currency? - How does Bitcoin work? - Will Bitcoin be used more in the future? - Will governments start trying to control Bitcoin? Leave a comment Contao Demo,', 17.94, 'eac8ad8877bf21ec9aece921ffc54457', '', 0x30, 'en'),
(4, 108, 1506266604, 'Infograghic: Immigration in California', 'http://localhost/ContaoMeta.0.1/index.php/infograghic-immigration-in-california.html', 'Infograghic: Immigration in California English lesson about immigration in California Illegal Immigration in California Is it a good thing or a bad thing? Take a few minutes to a look at the Infographic below. Read it and understand it. Your trainer will ask you the questions below Questions How can you sum up the information the graph is giving? Is the author for or against immigration? which new things did you learn from the graph? Do any of the facts in the graph reflect the situation in your country? What is your stance on illegal immigration? The source of the graph Look at the website of FAIRUS.ORG. What kind of organisation are they? A company, a pressure group or a think tank? Fair US Organization Let us know what you think What do you think will happen in the future. Some theories suggest there will be an emormous wealth shift. Meaning that China and Asia will become the rich modern countries, the new first world; whilst Europe and America become poor third world countries whose citizens mass-migrate to China in search of work. Leave a comment Comment by Franz Neumann | 2017-09-22 This is a very interesting question. The topic has changed some now. Trump is in power and is wanting to building a wall on the Mexico border and always shows himself to be a hostile to china. This is a wrong atttitude and shows the shifting tmes. China will be the next big world power and america cannot do anything about it. Americans in the south of USA are just blaming the bad times on immigrants, but it\'s not problem, as always. Reply by Samuel-Furneaux I don\'t really think Trump will build a wall and if he does it will be a shoddy shadow of his promise. Many claim that if Trump doesn\'t build it, he won\'t win the next election. This is another interesting question and if he really doesn\'t get it done, his success will depend on how well he can manipulate the voting population with fear and keep their phoney dream alive Contao Demo,', 16.21, 'a3d003dca10af2cb00f60f8b6c985bb0', '', 0x30, 'en'),
(5, 110, 1506266605, 'Infograghic: Social Media in Business', 'http://localhost/ContaoMeta.0.1/index.php/infograghic-social-media-in-business.html', 'Infograghic: Social Media in Business English lesson looking at the impact of social media on modern day businesses Social Media in Business Analyzing the infographic Take a few minutes to a look at the Infographic below. Read it and understand it. Your trainer will ask you the questions below Questions Why was this infographic created. Is it for commercial, informative or propaganda uses? Which countries have the highest social media reaches? What could be the possible reasons behind the differences? Is social media a force for good or bad in the business world Which new capabilities can social media give to marketing? Is the graphic helpful? Is it well laid out and reader friendly? Can a graph with so much information be a good or bad thing? How reliable is the graph and its sources?a Let us know what you think Leave a comment about your opinion. Imagine you are the head of Human Resources in a big company, you have the task of hiring a new manager. You have 400 applicants for the job and you have narrowed down all the applications to 30 of the best ones. Would you stalk them online by looking at their Facebook and Twitter accounts? Leave a comment Contao Demo,', 15.01, '3df87a63494ff977b7bf3b93833dcadc', '', 0x30, 'en'),
(6, 109, 1506266605, 'Infograghic: Who owns antarctica', 'http://localhost/ContaoMeta.0.1/index.php/infograghic-who-owns-antarctica.html', 'Infograghic: Who owns antarctica English lesson about who really owns the massive ice continent of Antarctica Infograghic: Who owns antarctica Analyzing the infographic Have a look at the infographic below. Take a few minutes to read it and understand it. After you have taken your time looking at it your trainer will ask you the questions posted below the image. Questions What information does the graphic present? What do you now know about Antarctica that you didn’t before? Does anybody really own Antarctica and why do so many countries lay claim to parts of it? If and when natural resources are discovered in Antarctica, will more countries try and claim territories? Could the next war be fought over Antarctica? How does territorial expansion into the continent affect the native wildlife? What other ways are there to make money off of the continent? The source of the graph Where does this graph come from and who wrote it? Why did they write it? Let us know what you think Do you think Antarctica will ever be home to towns and cities? When the climate gets warmer, the layers of rock underneath the icea will be uncovered, there will be less ice and more fishable water. At the moment, not many people live in arctic regions, many who do work in mining and oil extraction. Would you live there if you were offered a very high paid job on an oil platform? Leave a comment Contao Demo,', 15.44, 'e2f7d8933c9f4d056f13212f18118bba', '', 0x30, 'en'),
(7, 106, 1506266606, 'How will China affect our future?', 'http://localhost/ContaoMeta.0.1/index.php/how-will-china-affect-our-future-106.html', 'How will China affect our future? English lesson about the growing economic power of China How will China affect our future From communism to capitalism We all know that China is a country with a strong economy. It is a country who’s economy has grown very rapidly since the 1950’s. Before and during the second world war the country had been a very poor country. China always had it’s problems. It was invaded by the Japanese in WW2, it suffered horrible famine and a dysfunctional economy under Chairman Mao and Communism. Only the 1970’s did China being to accept and take on capitalism. China transformed itself under this new doctrine. One big had changed. People were now allowed to open their own businesses. On the rise China, a country with an enormous wealth of natural and human resources, was able to make rapid economic gains. It had billions of people who were used to working in horrible conditions. These people could now be used in factories. Those who bought the factories and started successful businesses became rich very fast. Today China is a country with a strong economy. Many people fear that it could overtake the economy of America (United States) and become the worlds biggest economy and the worlds strongest superpower! China 2.0 China knows that technology is the future. It knows that it will become the strongest industry in the world. It knows that when the oil runs out, America and the West will be up shit creak without a paddle. China invests heavily technology. Have you spoken to an Indian call center or seen stories of cheap Indian programmers working like factory workers, churning out program after program. China knows that India could be the next global superpower with which it will compete for world domination. India has a population of 1.1 Billion, while China has 1.3 Billion. India has many natural resources and lots of cheap labour. But India has many problems and that is why it’s not as powerful as China...yet. Workers of China’s technoogy industry are not like workers of Americas tech industry, Silicone Valley. In Silicone Valley, most workers are nowadays imported. Many come from Europe, China of course, India and Japan. In China however, most of the tech-talent is homegrown. Let us know what you think What do you think will happen in the future. Some theories suggest there will be an emormous wealth shift. Meaning that China and Asia will become the rich modern countries, the new first world; whilst Europe and America become poor third world countries whose citizens mass-migrate to China in search of work. Leave a comment Contao Demo,', 16.48, '9051171f671242f39d4b1c67e3cf7369', '', 0x30, 'en'),
(8, 107, 1506266607, 'A holiday in Cornwall', 'http://localhost/ContaoMeta.0.1/index.php/a-holiday-in-cornwall.html', 'A holiday in Cornwall English lesson about a holiday in Cornwall, England A holiday in Cornwall About Cornwall Cornwall is a rural region of South West England. It is one of the most beautiful places in England and is home to some of the most beautiful natural sites in Europe. Every year hundreds of thousands of tourists from Europe (mostly from Germany) visit Cornwall to experience the unique and comfortable climate and authentic/historic feel. Roleplay: The Whiteways Hotel You work for WhiteWays, a small hotel in the town of Penzance, Cornwall. Cornwall is a beautiful part of England that attracts many tourists every year. It is famous for its sandy beaches, beautiful nature, historic towns and its surf culture. Whitewavess is a new business and it needs a new website. Your job is to help the manager of WhiteWays to design his website. Describing the pictures The manager wants to use these pictures of the hotel and the surrounding scenary to make a magazine advert for WhiteWays. Use these words below to make a short paragraph about Cornwall for tourists. Beautiful Ugly Recharge Holiday Relax Kick back Visit Pleasure Energy Similar Online hotel description The manager of WhiteWays has just written a description of the hotel for the website. He wants you to put it on the hotel\'s website. However the manager does not speak very good English. Can you correct his writing? We are a hotel located in Penzance, Cornwall. We are welcome all guests from all country in the world. Here at our hotel we has much things to do for childs and for adults. In Penzance there are lots of restaurants and shops. The beach is also in the near and you can drive by train to other towns like St.Ives or Truro. At our hotel, you can make much fun and enjoy free eat in the morning. For breakfast, we have also a food card for children and also a card for older peoples who enjoy different eat. Analyzing the competition Now have a look at some of the local competition. The manager wants to know how he should design his website. What do you like about these website? Which things from them can the manager use for his website? Penzance BnB Shoreline Guest House Keignwin House Phone Roleplay Telephone Practise: Imagine you are calling as one of these guests. Now practise calling the hotel. What things do you want to know about the hotel and the town? What other questions do you have? James o\'Reily James is a man from York who loves to go to exotic places for his holidays. He hates cold temperatures and loves the sun and the beach. In the evening he likes to go to the cinema and eat in expensive restaurants. He has three young children and a wife who he is cheating on with 3 other women. Eric Hammond Eric works for a large software company in London. Eric is 28 years old and does not have a family, he lives in a basement apartment. He would like to go on holiday to meet other young people, get some sun and hopefully find a girlfriend. He loves to go surfing in the day and bowling in the night but he also loves to work on his computer and is secretly a hacker. He frequently wears womens clothes in private. Melissa Bates Melissa is 66 years old and she would like to come on holiday to Cornwall with her husband Bryan. Her husband is disabled and needs to use a wheelchair. Melissa would like to visit lots of museums and have a \"cultural holiday\". She is also an antiques collector and would like to get some antiques in Cornwall to add to her collection. She steals when nobody is looking. Leave a comment Contao Demo, , IMG_8505.JPG, IMG_8445.JPG, IMG_8691.JPG, beach.JPG, hotel1.JPG', 21.6, 'f367999e2998e8846872b8292c039b32', '', 0x30, 'en'),
(9, 91, 1506266608, 'Downsizing', 'http://localhost/ContaoMeta.0.1/index.php/downsizing.html', 'Downsizing The Office: Downsizing t\'s downsizing time and somebody must go The Scranton branch of Dunder Miflin has been given the news that it must downsize it\'s branch. Meaning it must let one of its members of staff go. Upper management has narrowed it down to two options. One of these people must be fired. Review their performance and decide which one should get the sack. Dwight Schrute Age 36 Department and job title Sales / Salesman Duration of employment 2000 to present Salary: $62,000 p.a Performance review grades: 2012: Excellent 2013: Excellent 2014: Poor 2015: Poor Last performance report Does not work well in teams and is often very arrogant. He does however work exceptionally well on his own. Supervisor\'s comments obsessive dedication to the company Driven by his desire to outperform Jim Always well dressed Strongest sales record Strange mannered. Some people find him off-putting Is often rude to other co-workers can often be a very distracting presence in the office Jim Halpert Age 29 Department and job title Sales / Salesman Duration of employment 2009 to present Salary: $59,000 p.a Performance review grades: 2012: Satisfactory 2013: Good 2014: Satisfactory 2015: Poor Last performance report Has been a good team player since the beginning of his employment but has become rather lax in his performance in recent months. He often fools around with Pam and Dwight who sit near him. He does have a solid sales performance but he has been a disruptive presence in the office as of late. Supervisor\'s comments Friendly, smart and liked by clients Has proven an effective team leader but is often hesitant to take charge Strong sales record Lacks motivation Very easily distracted and sometimes avoids working Often lacks professionalism Now present your decision to your Regional Manager Think of some more polite ways of saying \"fired\" Write a list of pros and cons for both Jim and Dwight. Then decide who to fire Here are some of the most common reasons to get fired. Which ones are the worst? Drug and/or alcohol abuse. High absenteeism rate Performing tasks slowly Dishonesty, evasion, or lack of integrity on the job. Inability to actually do assigned job tasks. Inconsistency - unreliable work and behaviors. Talking too much and conducting personal business at work Refusing to follow directions and orders Lying on a your resume/CV. Leave a comment Contao Demo', 16.92, '148cc21e09a1cc0ce2f54733f8f41a0e', '', 0x30, 'en'),
(10, 89, 1506266609, 'Is Macron the next Trump?', 'http://localhost/ContaoMeta.0.1/index.php/investing-in-thailand.html', 'Is Macron the next Trump? Investing in Thailand The task You have half a million pounds (£500,000) from your great uncle who recently passed away. Before his death, he always wanted to invest that money in the property market . But where should it be invested? He always said he wanted to buy property in Thailand. Now it’s up to you to make that savvy investment Thailand is a stunningly beautiful country and popular with western tourists. Thailand is a cheaper destination than most European countries. The country still has lots of problems with corruption, violent protests and narcotics. The economy of Thailand is doing very well and the country is developing at a fast pace and with a growing population and economy, Thai house prices are set to rise in the future. Here are some things currently on the market Traditional stilted Thai house near Chiang Mai Price: £200,000 200 squared meters 5 bedrooms 2 kitchens 1 living room 3 toilets Located in a small town with very few other expats. Bus and road connections to Chiang Mai, Bangkok and other Thai cities. Fully air conditioned with garden and driveway. Cheap apartments in North East Bangkok: 3 for Sale Price: 50,000 each 60 squared meters 1 bedroom 1 living room 1 toilet 1 kitchen Located in busy Bang Kok with lots of noisy roads and street vendors outside. Fully air conditioned. Unfurnished. No disabled access and no lifts. Small expat bar in central Chiang Mai Price:£150,000 140 square meters 1 main bar area 1 kitchen 2 toilets 1 store room Located in downtown Chiang Mai. A very popular city for British and European expats. Traditional stilted Thai house near Chiang Mai Price:£300,000 260 square meters 2 changing rooms for male and female 6 toilets altogether 4 shower units altogether Boxing ring, weights, training equipment all included Located in downtown Bangkok. The owner has gone bankrupt and is selling this Thai boxing club. It is traditionally used by Thai people with some famous Thai boxers training here occasionally. As Muay Thai kickboxing becomes more popular around the world, foreign interest in training in Thailand is picking up. Traditional stilted Thai house near Chiang Mai Price:£500,000 340 square meters 10 en suite guest rooms 2 offices 1 large basement 1 reception area 1 dining area 1 big kitchen 23 parking spaces Located in a small town with very few other expats. Bus and road connections to Chiang Mai, Bangkok and other Thai cities. Fully air conditioned with garden and driveway. Economic Data Look at the two diagrams below. What do they say about the state of the country and its economy? The economy of Thailand Tourism contributes significantly to the Thai economy, and the industry has benefited from the baht\'s depreciation and Thailand\'s stability. Tourist arrivals in 2002 reflected a 7.3 percent increase from the previous year. Tourism makes a larger contribution to Thailand\'s economy than that of any other Asian nation. Tourists come to Thailand for a variety of reasons, primarily for recreation on its beaches. With ongoing insurgency in the deep South, Bangkok has seen a large increase in tourism in recent years. An increase in tourism from other Asian countries has contributed to the country\'s economy, although the baht has recently strengthened relative to other currencies. In 2007, about 14 million tourists visited Thailand. The tourism sector includes a sex industry, although prostitution is illegal in Thailand. The easing of the monetary crisis, the renewed growth of the Chinese economy, the relatively stable internal political situation following the 2008Thai political crisis and the 2009 flu pandemic having less of an impact than initially feared changed the tourism outlook. Thailand experienced a 16 percent decrease in international visitors during the first six months of 2009, but the remainder of the year saw a return of foreign tourists (with a marked increase in November and December). The number of tourists in 2009 was estimated at nearly 14 million, a decrease of 4 percent from 2008.[72] Listen to the natives Listen to this article spoken by two native English speakers, Sam and Alana Leave a comment Contao Demo,', 21.76, 'c481468ee7feb3c1165261acc94b1854', '', 0x30, 'en'),
