(12, 67, 1506266611, 'The Expansion of Amazon', 'http://localhost/ContaoMeta.0.1/index.php/the-expansion-of-amazon.html', 'The Expansion of Amazon The 44th biggest company in the world ...on the way to being number 1? The expansion of Amazon Amazon, a word which once made people think of the rain forest in Brazil is now a household name and it is growing. Amazon started as a simple book retailer, which then branched out into selling other items, soon it had become a huge competitor to Ebay and now usually outsells them. Amazon has launched itself in 16 countries worldwide and sells more and more every year. How is it so successful? Many describe the business model of Amazon as one which \"is designed to strangle and kill off local business\", they do this by offering lower prices and fairly low delivery times. How do they do this? Offshore tax evasion and highly organised mass production style distribution centres. Workers in these centers often complain of low wages, limited toilet breaks and harsh working conditions. Amazon has recently began to expand its presence and many post offices and university campuses now have Amazon delivery stations Expanding into our lives Where can we now see Amazon? How about in your own home! Yes Amazon has recently launched its Amazon Echo. A device which sits somewhere in your home, perhaps your kitchen and living room. It listens to all conversation and its AI is activated when you talk to it by name, Alexa. It can be used for many things such as saving and reading shopping lists, reading audiobooks, playing music, asking general questions to Google and primarily, for shopping. Watch the Youtube video, a UK commercial for the Amazon Echo. A common remark is that the man has replaced his wife with the Amazon Alexa. The future But wait, Amazon has more plans to invade our lives. Not only does it want to use drones to deliver our packages, it has now started opening its own stores. Amazon Book stores are currently only operational in the USA, but they could soon be coming to you. As we have seen, Amazon has successfully been destroying it\'s competition since it\'s arrival onto the market. It began as a simple online counterpart, but now has a very real physical presence in our lives. Amazon book shops will be the only book shops if people do not support local traders, with its complex and efficient supply chain as well as it\'s massive size, Amazon will almost always be able to offer cheaper books than local shops. Leave a comment Contao Demo,', 17.31, '99a653637bf1cff84e6c13e42253ed1c', '', 0x30, 'en'),
