uture But wait, Amazon has more plans to invade our lives. Not only does it want to use drones to deliver our packages, it has now started opening its own stores. Amazon Book stores are currently only operational in the USA, but they could soon be coming to you. As we have seen, Amazon has successfully been destroying it\'s competition since it\'s arrival onto the market. It began as a simple online counterpart, but now has a very real physical presence in our lives. Amazon book shops will be the only book shops if people do not support local traders, with its complex and efficient supply chain as well as it\'s massive size, Amazon will almost always be able to offer cheaper books than local shops. Leave a comment Contao Demo,', 17.7, '19b97097c32940a0b91bdda6439702c6', '', 0x30, 'en'),
(14, 66, 1506266612, 'How Tourism changes the planet', 'http://localhost/ContaoMeta.0.1/index.php/how-tourism-changes-the-planet.html', 'How Tourism changes the planet What does tourism do to a planet... A worldwide overview Tourism has become a very big industry for many countries such as Spain, Thailand and Egypt to name a few. Many countries who decide to welcome tourists, have beautiful landscapes and beaches but few natural resources. For years, Spain has been one of the top tourist destinations in Europe and it has fully embraced this new source of income. After the 2008 financial crisis, countries like Greece, Portugal and Spain were some of the hardest hit countries due to their enormous debt which they could not repay. Spain still heavily relies on it\'s tourist industry to survive. It\'s other industries such as agriculture and manufacturing do not bring in the same type of money as tourism. Tourism has been good and bad for Spain. The main benefits are financial. It has brought money and many jobs to a country suffering from high unemployment. On the other hand, many complain of the destruction of natural beauty and of the Spanish culture. There are now hundreds of ugly tourist resorts all over Spain, many comprise almost entirely of English, German and Dutch tourists. Locals complain that their old towns have been transformed into modern money machines and that the huge tourist population causes traffic jams and overcrowding. The booming construction industry One big effect of the Spansh tourist industry has been the boom in construction. Second homes, hotels, roads, holiday resorts, theme parks and airports to shuttle in the tourists like farm animals. Many people have objected to the huge structures created and the destruction of nature which has followed. In the following example we see a picture of a the illegal Algarobbico Hotel near Almeria in Andalucia, Spain. The hotel was built in a protected natural park and was deemed illegal by the authorities. Many protested and construction stopped. The problem was that the permission to build was granted in the 1980\'s, but construction began in 2003, long after the area had become a natural park. There are hundreds of similar cases of illegal construction and horribly complicated beaurocracy. Cheap air travel One thing which has enabled tourists to come to a country in unprecedented numbers is the rise of cheap flying. Companies such as Ryanair and EasyJet are competing to be the biggest Budget Airline Comany . It\'s possible to get a flight from London to Barcelona for just 20 Euros! Many years ago flying was seen as a luxury. Something which only the very rich could afford. Airports were much smaller, more relaxed and usually more comfortable. Many people called this the Golden Age of air travel. Now it is affordable by almost anybody and it is constantly getting cheaper and cheaper and this means that more and more people will be coming on holiday every year. Case study Image you are working for the government of Spain at the Ministry of Tourism. You live in Valencia, this summer the city is expected to see double as many tourists as last year. People are coming from all over the world to see the Science Exhibition. You know that next year the numer of arrivals will double in the region of Valencia. You have 200 million Euros of borrowed money to invest, this means that your bosses need to see a return on the investment, otherwise you will lose your job. Option #1 : Invest the money in building new roads and train lines. Option #2 : Invest the money in creating new hotels and beach resorts Option #3 : Invest the money in expanding or rebuilding the current airport Option #4 : Give the money to local people to help improve their businesses Option #5 : Build a massive hotel complex on the outisde of town Now present your idea at a committee meeting and explain it\'s benefits over the other options. Leave a comment Contao Demo,', 19.21, '99b123bc194e34ffb023d53e41146785', '', 0x30, 'en'),
(15, 63, 1506266613, 'Is Macron the next Trump?', 'http://localhost/ContaoMeta.0.1/index.php/i-am-my-facebook-and-it-is-me.html', 'Is Macron the next Trump? I am my Facebook and it is me The power of Facebook.... Sometimes we just need to stop and ask ourselves, how did Facebook get so far? Before 2005 even, many people did not know about Facebook, yet alone have it. Now within the youngest generation. It seems like everybody has a Facebook and the trend of social media is not dying out. More and people are signing up with other social networks like Twitter, Instagram, Steam, Playstation Network and Xing. -Do you have a Facebook account? What do you use it for? -How often do you use your Facebook account? As a teenager, I grew up at a time when Facebook was becoming popular. The generation before me did not use Facebook and people only really began to use it around the ages of 14 to 15. Nowadays it seems children as young as 7 - 8 have Facebook. The amount of children with mobile phones is always increasing and with it the amount of Facebook Mobile users. What will Facebook look like in the future? If the current trend of digitalization continues, how will Facebook change? As the company conintue to be profitable, it will continue to develop itself. It will continue to develop new ways for the service to be exiting, it will add more things that humans enjoy like Virtual Reality (they already have plans for it), more integration with our devices and it will continue to use the huge amounts of data we give them. What about the data? This is the most important part. The data that Facebook collects about you, the data many people simply chose to forget about. Depending on the user and how much much they use Facebook, it knows where you are in the world, it knows who your friends are, it knows your opinions about things and it knows what you say to your friends. Conversations and voice calls are recorded, images processed and facially recognised, social patterns analysed; all this by a computer running complex algorithms. Are you worried about what Facebook can do with all your personal information? Do you think the government has access to your information through Facebook? How do you feel about computers analysing your personal information to give you suitable adverts?[ Leave a comment Contao Demo,', 16.76, 'e6b206dc98b6b903f341c128c43bc3ca', '', 0x30, 'en'),
(16, 60, 1506266613, 'Is Macron the next Trump?', 'http://localhost/ContaoMeta.0.1/index.php/is-macron-the-next-trump.html', 'Is Macron the next Trump? Is Macron the next Trump The problems with Macron Macron has been elected the new president of France. Emmanuel Macron won the 2017 French elections against Marine Le Pen with 73% of the votes. Marine Le Pen was seen as a more radical, right-wing politician who wanted France to leave the European Union. But who is this man and is he similar to Donald Trump? He is similar to president Trump in many ways. Both men have a background in business and finance, both presented themselves as \"political outsiders\" and both were unique candidates in their own way. Le Pen would be the first female president of France and Macron, with a background in investment banking and politics, created his own political party called En Marche and will be the youngest French head of state since Napoleon. Does Macron think like Trump? Macron is a very rich man who made a lot of money with investment banking at Rotschild & Cie Banque. The Rotschild family and its companies are infamous for it\'s enormous wealth and global political power. Many claim they form the \"Hidden Hand\", an elite group of extremely wealthy people, families and companies who really rule the world. Being a successful businessman like Macron or Trump means they must think and act according to simple rules 1) Be open for negotiation, keep in mind needs of all participants 2) Try to turn enemies into friends, war is too expensive 3) Never dwell on your mistakes, business first. Macron\'s wife is 24 years older than him Many find it strange how Macron is married toBriget Trogneux, who is 24 years older than him. Their love began when Macron was a 16 year old schoolboy and Bridget was his drama teacher at the school. His parents made him change schools as they were worried about this strange love affair, it didn\'t work and they married in 2007. This strange love affair contributed again to Macron\'s outsider image, others claim it is a sham marriage or that Macron is actually gay. In a way, this strange love affair a little similar to Melania Trump. For one, they both have big age differences to their husbands who are both the youngest and oldest ever presidents of their countries respectively. The media wanted Macron to win Unlike Trump in Ameria however, Macron was the media favourite. Macron is pro business and the media is big business. It is a business with enormous social power and in this case, it managed to contribute to the new president\'s victory. The media can influence any election by p ainting their favourite candidate in a good light and making others look worse. In the example below, we can clearly see Le Pen being compared with Donald Trump. The media has done nothing but make Trump look bad all accross the world. People generally have negative feelings towards Trump. Despite Macron being more similar to trump in less obvious ways, the media used Le Pen\'s more radical opinions and even her hair to compare her to Trump. Leave a comment Contao Demo', 16.95, 'f6cd1793e1c67d11765b4d4ba56f2e04', '', 0x30, 'en'),
