(35, 10, 1506266627, 'About Me', 'http://localhost/ContaoMeta.0.1/index.php/about.html', 'About Me About Samuel Furneaux the author of this page Home Hi I\'m Sam Nice to see that somebody is reading about me! I’m a man from England who loves to work and travel. I work as a freelance web developer and online English teacher. My hobbies are travelling, languages and meeting different people. I like to be different and don’t really care what other people think about me. I’m currently living in the south of Spain. Sometimes I sleep on mountains next to castles, sometimes in abandoned villas and sometimes in cosy AirBNBs. I also spent 3 weeks in a stunningly beautiful hippy village smoking weed and taking LSD. I live the nomad life and hate to be normal, boring or politically correct. The world needs to change, and we should be able to say what we believe. I channel my inspiration from all my travels and crazy activities into giving fun and exciting English lessons. English Teaching I love to teach languages. I have been teaching English for the last 4 years and have enjoyed every moment of it. My lessons are funny and entertaining. That\'s always been important to me, without it I would have no passion for my teaching and my clients would be bored and learn nothing. After years of private lessons and professional teaching, I decided to start teaching online; this way I could see the world and keep my students. My relatonship to my students is also very important, having regular lessons and staying in contact is essential to have a productive and warm relationship. Online Lessons I moved to online teaching about 1 year ago. At that time I had no website of my own and advertised myself through Ebay Kleinanzeige, a German listing website, like Ebay but for jobs and local items. I always wanted to have my own website that was fully my own, no Wordpress bullshit, all me. So I began to teach myself web design, creating very basic pages and then moving on to more complex things. The first version of SamLernen was released in December 2016 and it was raw coded 100% by me. It was very buggy, unresponsive and slow. After a long and painful road of learning how to code and build complex database driven websites, I presented SamLernen to the world. It has many features which are essential for my lessons, the most important and basic being an appointment calendar and a secure place to upload and view content, a place that was our very own! Now we have all this, it\'s working and it makes life a hell of a lot easier. Enjoy using the websites, theres more to come :D Teaching in Germany When I was 19, I left my home of Penzance, England for Germany. It was a lot of fun and very exciting. It was my first big adventure. I got my TEFL qualification and went to work teaching at language schools in Hannover. I also worked at the university . I found it more fun giving private English lessons. I could talk about what I want and cut out the boring shit that the language schools made me teach. I later worked for Continental teaching business English as well as some other small engineering firms where I taught and translated. Contao Demo,', 17.94, '8752fa87f4ce36f0c2dfad60e58911a7', '', 0x30, 'en'),
